<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="eyebrow">Brand &amp; Product Marketing &middot; Bay Area</p>
      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        I ask <span class="campfire">"what if."</span><br />Then I make it <span class="amber">real</span>.
      </h1>
      <div class="hero-body">
        <p>
          Most people use "what if" as a creative exercise. I use it as a starting point. The real
          question isn't what's possible. It's why we haven't done it yet, what's actually holding
          the business back, and whether anyone is willing to say it out loud.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's what I do. I find the root problem, name it clearly, and build the case for
          change, in whatever language the room needs to hear. I'm a marketer who leads with
          courage and clarity, and I'm looking for high-ownership marketing roles in tech.
        </p>
        <p>
          As a business consultant at Citibank rotating across teams, I learned how to start from
          zero: walk into an unfamiliar context, find the problem, find the people, and deliver. As
          a Senior Brand Manager at P&amp;G, I learned how to challenge what everyone accepts: I
          questioned why established brands were declining, named the constraints nobody wanted to
          name, and built the argument for change. At Kellogg, I learned that the best insight
          means nothing if you can't move people. At Adobe and OneCalla, I applied all of it to
          tech: product, data, funnels, and growth, a faster-moving world that I'm built for.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm not the loudest voice in the room. I'm the one who sees which question actually
          matters, says it plainly, and doesn't stop until something changes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-image">
      <img src="/images/headshot.jpeg" alt="Junior Hou" class="headshot" />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: 5rem var(--pad-x) 4rem;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-w);
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 380px;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hero-headline {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .campfire {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .italic {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .amber {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .hero-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  .hero-image {
    position: sticky;
    top: 5rem;
  }

  .headshot {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 3 / 4;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 58% center;
    display: block;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hero-image {
      position: static;
      max-width: 280px;
    }
  }
</style>
